The paper deals with algorithms for computing shortest paths in a polygon, which is a classic problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces new tools and techniques for solving the problem, which could be of interest to researchers in other areas of computer science. This makes cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the problem of computing shortest paths in a polygon has applications in robotics and control theory, which could make cs.SY (Systems and Control) a relevant sub-category.
